## **TL;DR: Everything You Need to Know About Oval Cut Diamonds**

An oval cut diamond is an elliptical brilliant-cut diamond featuring 57–58 facets arranged in the same radiating pattern as a round brilliant — but stretched into an elongated outline that delivers 10–15% more apparent surface area than a round of equal carat weight at 15–25% lower price. It is the fastest-growing engagement ring shape in 2026, with approximately 25% of all couples now choosing oval over round.

**Live 2026 price snapshot:**

-   1ct natural E-VS1 Ideal Cut GIA starts at **[$5,720](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/22756538?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational)**
-   1ct natural D-IF Ideal Cut GIA: **[$7,240](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/28218235?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational)** (outlier: **[$9,510](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/14660317?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational)**)
-   2ct natural E-VS1 Ideal Cut GIA starts at **[$22,630](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/28501958?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational)**
-   3ct natural D-VVS1 Ideal Cut GIA: **[$72,790](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/26140444?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational)**
-   1ct lab-grown E-IF Ideal Cut IGI: **[$1,790](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/28238579?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational)**
-   2ct lab-grown D-IF Ideal Cut IGI: **[$5,490](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/28558309?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational)**
-   3ct lab-grown D-FL Ideal Cut IGI: **[$11,070](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/28558441?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational)**

**The one thing every oval buyer must know:** Every oval cut diamond has a bow-tie effect — a dark shadow across the widest section of the stone. The severity ranges from invisible to grotesque. You cannot evaluate bow-tie severity from a GIA certificate or a static product image. You must watch the 360° HD video before purchasing any oval cut diamond.

**Buy an oval cut if:**

-   You want 10–15% more apparent size than round at 15–25% lower price
-   You want the most popular trending engagement ring shape in 2026
-   You want a finger-lengthening effect — the elongated outline extends the visual length of the finger
-   You want brilliant-cut sparkle in a distinctive non-round silhouette

**Consider a different shape if:**

-   You want maximum guaranteed brilliance without bow-tie risk — round brilliant
-   You want a step-cut optical aesthetic — emerald or Asscher
-   You want absolute minimum price per carat — cushion or radiant

